---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Option B — Waseda" activeTab="waseda">
  <div class="mb-8">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
      <span class="tier-badge bg-waseda/20 text-waseda text-sm">B — Realistic</span>
    </div>
    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold">Waseda University</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-lg mt-2">School of Fundamental Science & Engineering — Mechanical Engineering, English-based degree</p>
  </div>

  <blockquote>
    Top-tier Japanese private university. English-based 4-year BE in Mechanical Engineering. Excellent calendar fit (Sept 2028 entry, 3-month gap from June graduation). ~USD 12k/year tuition — <strong>about 1/5 the cost of Melbourne</strong>. Already in Japan, so visa is a transfer not a fresh application. Competitive: average admit has SAT 1480.
  </blockquote>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2>The university</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>Waseda University</strong> is one of Japan's two top-ranked private universities (with Keio). Globally QS top 200 — but inside Japan its prestige with employers is enormous, especially for engineering and business. The Tokyo campus (Nishi-Waseda for engineering) is in central Tokyo with strong industry links to Japanese manufacturing (Toyota, Honda, Mitsubishi Heavy, Sony).
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2>The program</h2>
    <p>
      <strong>School of Fundamental Science and Engineering (FSE)</strong> — English-based Degree Program in Mechanical Engineering.
      4-year BE, fully taught in English, no Japanese required for coursework or admission.
    </p>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="content-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Year</th><th>Focus</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td class="text-waseda font-bold">1</td><td>Math, physics, basic mechanics, intro CS, English academic skills</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="text-waseda font-bold">2</td><td>Thermodynamics, fluid mechanics, materials, design</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="text-waseda font-bold">3</td><td>Specialisation electives, lab work, mechatronics</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="text-waseda font-bold">4</td><td>Capstone research project under a faculty advisor</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2>Pros and cons</h2>
    <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
      <div class="card border-green-900/40">
        <h3 class="mt-0 text-green-400 text-base">Pros</h3>
        <ul class="text-sm space-y-2 list-none pl-0 mb-0">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5">+</span> <strong>Excellent calendar fit</strong> — Sept 2028 start, 3 months after graduation</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5">+</span> <strong>~1/5 the cost of Melbourne</strong></li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5">+</span> Strong Japan-employer prestige (Sony, Honda, Toyota)</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5">+</span> 4 years to BE (not 5 like Melbourne)</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5">+</span> No interview required — document-based</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5">+</span> Already in Japan — no fresh visa, no overseas move</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-green-500 mt-0.5">+</span> Strong scholarship pipeline (~40% of intl. students get some award)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="card border-red-900/40">
        <h3 class="mt-0 text-red-400 text-base">Cons</h3>
        <ul class="text-sm space-y-2 list-none pl-0 mb-0">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-500 mt-0.5">&minus;</span> <strong>Highly competitive</strong> — average admit ~SAT 1480, ~TOEFL 95+</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-500 mt-0.5">&minus;</span> Tokyo cost of living is high</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-500 mt-0.5">&minus;</span> Curriculum is denser/more rigid — less elective freedom</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-500 mt-0.5">&minus;</span> English-track cohort is small</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-500 mt-0.5">&minus;</span> Japanese employers may expect conversational Japanese after graduation</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-500 mt-0.5">&minus;</span> Less internationally recognised outside Japan/Asia</li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-2"><span class="text-red-500 mt-0.5">&minus;</span> Personal statement carries a lot of weight</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2>Admission requirements</h2>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="content-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Requirement</th><th>Detail</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Diploma</td><td>US High School Diploma (OCSI qualifies)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>GPA</td><td>No published minimum; admits typically <strong>&ge; 3.7</strong></td></tr>
          <tr><td>Standardized test</td><td><strong>SAT 1480+</strong> / ACT 32 / IB 38 (2025 admit average)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>English</td><td>TOEFL iBT <strong>95+</strong> or IELTS 7.0+ (possible waiver for OCSI)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Japanese</td><td><strong>Not required</strong></td></tr>
          <tr><td>EJU</td><td><strong>Not required</strong> for English program</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Personal statement</td><td>"Statement of Purpose" required</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Recommendations</td><td>1-2 from teachers (math/science emphasised)</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Interview</td><td><strong>None</strong> — document-based admission</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2>Cost</h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4">2026 published rates — verify in 2027</p>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="content-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Item</th><th>Per year</th><th>4-year total</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Tuition (engineering)</td><td>~&yen;1,750,000 - 1,850,000</td><td>~&yen;7,200,000</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Admission fee (year 1)</td><td>~&yen;200,000</td><td>~&yen;200,000</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Living costs in Tokyo</td><td>~&yen;1,500,000 - 1,800,000</td><td>~&yen;6,600,000</td></tr>
          <tr><td>National Health Insurance</td><td>~&yen;20,000</td><td>~&yen;80,000</td></tr>
          <tr class="font-bold text-white">
            <td>Approximate 4-year total</td>
            <td></td>
            <td class="text-waseda">~&yen;14,000,000 (~USD 93,000)</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div class="card mt-4">
      <h3 class="mt-0 text-base">Scholarships worth applying for</h3>
      <ul class="text-sm space-y-1 mb-0">
        <li><strong>Waseda Scholarship for Privately Financed International Students</strong> — partial tuition reduction</li>
        <li><strong>Waseda Tsubasa Pre-Arrival Scholarship</strong> — &yen;600,000/year for top applicants</li>
        <li><strong>JASSO Honors Scholarship</strong> — &yen;48,000/month</li>
        <li><strong>MEXT</strong> — full tuition + &yen;117,000/month stipend if awarded</li>
        <li class="text-gray-500 italic">~40% of international students receive some scholarship</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2>Application timeline</h2>
    <div class="mermaid-container">
      <pre class="mermaid">
gantt
    title  Waseda FSE Mechanical (English) — Application Timeline (Sept 2028 entry)
    dateFormat  YYYY-MM-DD
    axisFormat  %b %Y

    section Preparation
    SAT prep                          :2026-09-01, 240d
    AP Calc AB + AP Physics (G11)     :2026-08-17, 280d
    First SAT (target 1450+)          :milestone, 2027-05-01, 0d
    TOEFL iBT (target 95+)            :milestone, 2027-07-15, 0d
    SAT retake if needed              :milestone, 2027-10-02, 0d
    AP Calc BC + AP Physics 2 (G12)   :2027-08-16, 280d

    section Application
    Begin Statement of Purpose        :2027-10-01, 60d
    Request recommendation letters    :milestone, 2027-11-15, 0d
    Application window OPENS          :milestone, 2028-01-08, 0d
    Submit application                :milestone, 2028-01-25, 0d
    Application window CLOSES         :milestone, 2028-02-10, 0d

    section Decision & Enrolment
    Decision notification             :milestone, 2028-03-31, 0d
    Accept offer + tuition deposit    :milestone, 2028-04-15, 0d
    Status of Residence transfer      :2028-05-01, 90d
    Tokyo accommodation               :2028-06-01, 90d
    OCSI graduation                   :milestone, 2028-05-26, 0d
    Semester begins                   :milestone, 2028-09-21, 0d
      </pre>
    </div>

    <h3>Key dates</h3>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="content-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Date</th><th>Action</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td class="whitespace-nowrap font-mono text-xs">Sep 2026</td><td>Start SAT prep; lock in AP Calc AB + AP Physics for Grade 11</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="whitespace-nowrap font-mono text-xs">May 2027</td><td>First SAT — target 1450+</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="whitespace-nowrap font-mono text-xs">Jul 2027</td><td>TOEFL iBT — target 95+</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="whitespace-nowrap font-mono text-xs">Oct 2027</td><td>SAT retake if first attempt &lt; 1450</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="whitespace-nowrap font-mono text-xs">Oct-Nov 2027</td><td>Draft Statement of Purpose</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="whitespace-nowrap font-mono text-xs">Nov 15, 2027</td><td>Request recommendation letters</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="whitespace-nowrap font-mono text-xs">Jan 8, 2028</td><td>Application window opens</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="whitespace-nowrap font-mono text-xs">~Jan 25, 2028</td><td>Submit application (don't wait for deadline)</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="whitespace-nowrap font-mono text-xs">Feb 10, 2028</td><td>Application window closes</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="whitespace-nowrap font-mono text-xs">~Mar 31, 2028</td><td>Decision notification</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="whitespace-nowrap font-mono text-xs">Apr 15, 2028</td><td>Accept offer + pay deposit</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="whitespace-nowrap font-mono text-xs">May-Jul 2028</td><td>Status of Residence renewal/change</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="whitespace-nowrap font-mono text-xs">~Sep 21, 2028</td><td>Semester begins</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2>Application checklist</h2>
    <ul class="checklist">
      <li>Confirm OCSI sends transcripts directly to Waseda</li>
      <li>Take SAT — target 1450+</li>
      <li>Take TOEFL iBT — target 95+</li>
      <li>AP scores: Calculus + Physics + one more, all 4+</li>
      <li>Statement of Purpose (~800 words): why engineering, why Waseda, what experience led here</li>
      <li>Two recommendation letters (math/physics teacher + one other)</li>
      <li>Activities list — sustained engagement matters more than variety</li>
      <li>Passport + Japan residence card scans</li>
      <li>Submit via Waseda's online portal</li>
      <li>Application fee: ~&yen;35,000</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2>Russian passport — practical notes</h2>
    <div class="card border-surface-600">
      <ul class="text-sm space-y-2 list-none pl-0 mb-0">
        <li><strong>Zero issues</strong> for Japanese university enrolment.</li>
        <li>Ivan is already a Japan resident. Status of Residence will change from "Dependent" (or current status) to "Student" — routine procedure handled by Waseda's international office.</li>
        <li>MEXT scholarship eligibility intact — Russia has diplomatic relations with Japan.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="mb-12">
    <h2>Realistic verdict</h2>
    <div class="card border-waseda/30">
      <p class="mb-3">Waseda is the <strong>single best-balanced option</strong> of the three:</p>
      <ul class="text-sm space-y-2 mb-4">
        <li>Most likely to be <strong>financially sustainable</strong> (~USD 93k total vs Melbourne's ~USD 290k)</li>
        <li><strong>Best calendar fit</strong> (no gap year)</li>
        <li><strong>Highest prestige per dollar</strong></li>
        <li><strong>Lowest friction</strong> — already in Japan</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-3">
        The challenge: <strong>the bar is high</strong>. SAT 1450+ and a sharp personal statement are needed.
        If Ivan only reaches SAT 1300-1400, Waseda becomes a reach and Shibaura IGP becomes the practical Japan option.
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm text-waseda font-semibold mb-0">
        This is the option to optimise for. The preparation that gets him here will also unlock both Melbourne and Shibaura automatically.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
